This is almost certainly the photograph by John Degotardi senior exhibited at the 1866 Intercolonial Exhibition in Melbourne, and described on the State Library of Victoria catalogue as follows - &quot;Includes the Gasworks chimney bearing a plaque reading 'GASWORKS 1840' and a gasometer made of iron in the foreground. Balmain can be seen across the water.&quot;

Gas Light Company's Head Station on the Eastern Shore of Darling Harbour / the back ground shewing portions of the Town of Balmain. / Sydney. N.S.Wales. 1866.
